\begin{abstract}
We study the convergence of the Jacobi iterative method for symmetric positive definite linear systems. We establish an explicit upper bound on the spectral radius of the Jacobi iteration matrix in terms of the extremal eigenvalues of the coefficient matrix, and show that this bound is tight. Our result sharpens existing estimates and extends to a broader class of problems than previously considered.
\end{abstract}

